        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 3:53PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 353 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Antelope Springs, or 11 miles northeast of Fort Morgan, and is
stationary.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and half inch size
hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Brush, Hillrose, Snyder, Antelope Springs and Union.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
